HTTP GET Hoover logs all HTTP GET requests that flow through a specified local network interface.

Doesn't sound too useful?  What if you pair it with an ARP spoof?  :)

Notes:
	1. Written/Works on MacOS (should work on Linux too?).

Dependencies/Setup:
	1. Install RVM (http://beginrescueend.com/).
	2. Install Ruby v1.9.2.

Usage: 
	sudo -E ./go [interface]

i.e. sudo -E ./go en0
